THE COUNCIL RECEIVED A FAVORABLE TAX DETERMINATION LETTER FROM THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE (IRS) DATED AUGUST 1980 THAT STATES THAT THE COUNCIL IS EXEMPT FROM THE PAYMENT OF INCOME TAXES ON ITS EXEMPT ACTIVITIES UNDER SECTION 501(c)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC). HOWEVER, ANY ACTIVITIES UNRELATED TO THE ENTITY'S TAX EXEMPTION WOULD BE SUBJECT TO APPLICABLE INCOME TAXES. THE COUNCIL REPORTS NO SUCH ACTIVITIES FOR THE FISCAL YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2023. THE COUNCIL'S FEDERAL EXEMPT ORGANIZATION TAX RETURNS (FORM 990) ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AFTER THEY WERE FILED.
FORMER EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS PAID ON A NON-QUALIFIED DEFERRED COMPENSATION PLAN AS RETIREMENT.
A DRAFT COPY OF THE FEDERAL FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE PRESIDENT OF THE BOARD. UPON APPROVAL, THE 990 IS SIGNED AND FILED WITH THE IRS.
